The paper discusses the role of time-frequency methods in communication systems, including topics such as dispersive channels, OFDM, information-theoretic limits, and system identification and channel estimation. These topics are all related to information theory, signal processing, and networking, which are covered by the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SI, cs.SP, and cs.NI. Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
